-- Germany Wins Women’s European Soccer Title for 6th Straight Time
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-07-28T17:00:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-28/germany-wins-women-s-european-soccer-title-for-6th-straight-time.html
Germany  soccer captain Nadine
Angerer saved two penalty kicks as her team won the European
women’s championship for the sixth successive time, beating
Norway 1-0.  Substitute Anja Mittag scored in the 49th minute of the
final in Solna,  Sweden , rounding off a passing movement.  Trine Ronning had seen her spot-kick saved in the first
half, and Solveig Gulbrandsen’s penalty was blocked by Angerer
in the 61st minute, both kicks being awarded for fouls. Norway’s
Ada Hegerberg had a goal disallowed for offside in the 65th
minute.  Eight-time winner Germany began its current sequence of
titles in 1995.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  